===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|psc}}: semantic {{zh-l|*車|chariot}} + phonetic {{zh-l|*勹}}. The phonetic component here is not {{och-l|勹}}, but the original form of {{och-l|螾}}, which also acts as the phonetic component of {{och-l|旬}}, {{och-l|勻}} and {{och-l|云}}. 

The {{w|Shuowen Jiezi}} interprets it as {{Han compound|車|勹|ls=ic|t1=cart; chariot|t2=to surround|nocap=yes}}.

===Etymology===
Etymology not clear. Perhaps cognate with {{cog|bo|གཡུལ||army; battle}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Alternatively, it is a derivation from {{och-l|運|to move}}, or related to {{och-l|群}}.

