===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|いくさ|yomi=k}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=いくさ|-}}, first attested in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' (720 {{CE}}).

The ''iku'' part is possibly derived from either {{m|ja|射くう|tr=ikuu||to [[shoot]] (an [[arrow]])|pos=obsolete}}, {{m|ja|的|tr=ikuha||[[target]]|pos=archaic}}, or classical verb {{m|ja|生く|tr=iku||to [[exist]], [[live]]; [[bring]] to [[life]]}}. The ''iku-'' in the first and second [[etymon|etyma]] appear to be [[cognate]].

The final ''sa'' is likely from {{m|ja|矢|tr=sa||[[arrow]]|pos=obsolete}} or {{m|ja|さ|tr=-sa|pos=suffix attached to verbs to refer to the time that the activity is done, or to nouns indicating [[direction]]}}.

